history.content: I double major in Applied Math + CS. I declared Applied Math first. I took Math 55 instead of CS 70 and successfully declared CS. Math 55 does have probability but is very very basic. If you want to take EECS 126, please take 70 instead of 55. To prepare for classes like CS 170, I recommend 70 over 55.

If I double major in CS + Math, will Math 55 really work in place of CS 70 when declaring CS (given that the Math major is declared first)? Or will I still have to take CS 70 since Math 55 doesn't have Probability? I'm a little confused since I've gotten some different answers to this question. Any info would be greatly appreciated!
